According to the FL intensity of FA-Cu NCs declined or even quenched in the presence of rifampicin, an analysis platform for the sensing of rifampicin was established. The detection time of this sensing system was 20 s (Fig. S6).The fluorescence spectra of FA-Cu NCs with different rifampicin concentrations (0–100 μM) were exhibited in Fig. 4
                        A. When the concentrations of rifampicin rose from 0 μM to 100 μM, the FL intensities of sensing system gradually decreased. With rifampicin concentrations increasing from 0.5 μM to 100 μM, the ln(F0/F) value displayed an excellent linear relationship with the rifampicin amounts (F and F0 refers to the FL intensity of FA-Cu NCs with and without rifampicin). The linear equation of ln(F0/F) = 0.024[Q] + 0.1399 was obtained, and the detection limit was 0.073 μM based on the formula LOD = 3σ/k (Fig. 4B). Compared with the existing sensing strategies, the preparation of FA-Cu NCs demanded one step reaction. Additionally, the preparation conditions of FA-Cu NCs were mild, such as lower temperature and moderate pH value. This method had a relatively wider linear detection range or lower detection limit (Table 1
                        ).
